      "content": "You should absolutely be careful with that grapefruit juice and your atorvastatin. Grapefruit juice can interfere with how your body processes statins, potentially leading to dangerously high levels of the drug in your system. To be safe, you should definitely skip the juice with your medication and stick to water or a small amount of orange juice instead.",
