      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"superfood\" benefits are great, but the drug interaction is a serious medical issue, not a minor dietary preference. Even a small amount of grapefruit juice can significantly alter how your body metabolizes atorvastatin, so timing it away from the pill is not a safe workaround. You must avoid combining them, or at the very least, wait a full four hours between the juice and the medication.",
      "source": "target",
